data.name: Clapping Music solo snare drums version (Steve Reich cover)
data.loading_phrase: This song was performed live by one person with two snares. It is charted on yellow and blue toms, yellow is the left snare in panning, and blue is the right one. This is how it works in the original song with clapping, it's the same with the snares in this cover: "One performer (snare) claps a basic rhythm, a variation of the fundamental African bell pattern in 12/8 time (6/4 at 193 bpm in this chart, for simplicity's sake), for the entirety of the piece. The other (snare) claps the same pattern, but after every 12 bars (measures) shifts by one eighth note to the right (earlier). The two performers (snares) continue this until the second performer (snare) has shifted 12 eighth notes and is hence playing the pattern in unison with the first performer (snare) again, as at the beginning."
